<item>
            <title>[SHIRO-747] FirstSuccessfulStrategy doesn&apos;t properly short circuit</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SHIRO-747</link>
                <project id="12310950" key="SHIRO">Shiro</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SHIRO-669&quot; title=&quot;Included a boolean flag in FirstSuccessfulStrategy to break after first successful authentication&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SHIRO-669&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SHIRO-669&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; supposedly added a method to skip subsequent authentications if one had already succeeded. But it doesn&apos;t work; it conditions throwing the ShortCircuitIterationException in beforeAttempt() in part on the PrincipalCollection being empty, which it will (properly) not be if an authentication has succeeded. I believe the check should be that the it is &lt;b&gt;not&lt;/b&gt; empty. Was this tested??&lt;/p&gt;</description>
